<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCE6A71FD2297D11D53B83F" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCE6A71FD2297D11D53B83F" blockId="53.[732,1329,278,701]" lastBlockId="53.[121,1332,708,2437]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCE6A71FD2297D11A01BA9B" baseAuthorityName="Bobrinskii" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[734,1025,392,425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alaschanicus">Hypsugo alaschanicus</taxonomicName>
is generally considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCE6A71FBFD97E91A69BAE3" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[1025,1129,432,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
, but morphological and genetic data support its species status; nevertheless, they are closely related genetically, and further work is needed to clarify their relationship. Taxa coreensis and velox are both considered synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCE6A71FD2294C51DB3B98F" baseAuthorityName="Bobrinskii" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[734,947,668,701]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alaschanicus">H. alaschanicus</taxonomicName>
here, although both may represent valid subspecies, based on limited morphological differences; the formeris occasionally treated as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
